Before running both algorithms, you need to do the following:

################################

1. Download fastText from:
   $ wget https://github.com/facebookresearch/fastText/archive/v0.2.0.zip
2. $ unzip v0.2.0.zip
3. $ cd fastText-0.2.0
4. $ make
5. $ python3 setup.py install

#################################

1. Download fastText_multilingual from (clone the repo):
   $ https://github.com/Babylonpartners/fastText_multilingual
2. Make sur to add the folder containing the module to PYTHONPATH (otherwise cannot be imported)
TODO 3. Put the subfolder "aligned_matrices" inside the folder expcode/fastText


#################################
Download nltk:
1. $ pip3 install nltk
2. $ sudo python -m nltk.downloader all (MIGHT HAVE TO RUN 2.1 on Mac OSX)
2.1 $ /Applications/Python\ 3.6/Install\ Certificates.command

#################################

Other dependencies:
- scipy
- numpy
- pickle
- matplotlib

#################################

Must also do the following:

1. Download the europarl.fr-en dataset at:
   http://www.statmt.org/europarl/
2. Tokenize using the script tokenize.py
TODO 3. Add the tokenized files to a subfolder "dataset" inside the folder "expcode"





